    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "the \"small and beautiful\" stuff feels like a joke though. like just putting a bandaid on a severed limb. how can you tell me it's worth it when we're literally watching the systems that support all life collapse? it feels less like \"finding meaning\" and more like just prolonging the inevitable. it's hard to see staying around as anything other than just being a witness to a slow-motion catastrophe.",
